The collection and processing of personal data is subject to the rules laid down in the Data Protection Law. As a general note, personal data processing operations may only be undertaken once one of the following requirements are met:

lawfulness;
consent;
performance of a contract;
legitimate interests, public interests, vital interests of data subject or legal duty.&nbsp;

Moreover, as previously stated, there are some cases (referred to above) in which the collection and processing of personal data is subject to prior authorization from the data protection authority.Last modified 8 Jan 2022
				
			